  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Dice the tofu into bite-sized chunks. Zest the lime. Add the tofu to a bowl along with the gochujang, soy sauce and lime zest. Toss to coat and set aside to marinate while you prep the rest."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Dice the mango into small pieces. If you'd prefer your quinoa warm, heat it now following pack instructions. Pick the coriander."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a small bowl, mix the Greek yoghurt with the sriracha and lime juice. Season with a pinch of salt and pepper."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Time to build your bowl. Divide the quinoa between Tupperware containers and top with the marinated tofu, mango, edamame and kimchi. Drizzle over the sriracha yoghurt and finish with a scattering of coriander and sesame seeds. Box up and pop in the fridge, ready for when you need it. These keep for 3 days in the fridge."
    }
  ],
